    <subfield code="u">http://inspirehep.net/record/1343646/files/fig1.png</subfield>
    <subfield code="y">00000 (Color online) A schematic diagram of a device supporting two MFs in a SOC nanowire with proximity-induced exchange field and superconductivity. The wire is sandwiched between two easy-axis ferromagnets: one with a uniform magnetization and the other with a DW. In the right portion of the wire, where the magnetizations of the two ferromagnets are parallel, the net exchange field engenders the topological region, fomenting MFs at locations marked by A and B. The temperature-gradient induces magnon drag in the $x$ direction, which drives the DW and its accompanying MF at A to the hotter region.</subfield>
